metadata.name: MONKIEZ #35
metadata.description:
This collection features a quirky monkey who loves to eat all kinds of Japanese food! 

The cheerful monkey enjoys exploring and indulging in the diverse flavors of Japanese cuisine, from ramen to sushi, while soaking in the relaxing hot springs. 

The collection is filled with vibrant colors, exciting textures, and intricate details that bring the cheerful monkey and its love of Japanese food to life.

metadata.name: BWEEPS  #192
metadata.description:
A minimalist, black-and-white generative profile picture (PFP) created to commemorate one-year anniversary of Bwople project by Gengoya. The artwork is derived from an initial sketch of Bwople which, despite being not the one that was chosen, still managed to captivate interests. The project provides a unique glimpse into an alternate universe in which Bwople could have been represented.

All images are hand-drawn work by Gengoya and composed by Vector Recite using PureSpider's fxhash-pfp maker tool.

To download the full size image on fx(hash):
- Click "open" below the image
- Left click on the image, a "Download image" button will appear on the bottom right.
- Click the "Download image" button.

metadata.name: Experiment No.4 - Theory #66
metadata.description:
Results of an old experiment continue to be inputs to the new experiments!

”Experiment No.4” is a generative artwork coded by True Neutral, January 2023.

Total 26 palettes with 15 vanilla filter!

Special thanks to @Clete, @Neppenthe, @Hiceku

Press "S" to save a .jpg of your token in Open Live.

metadata.name: Dopamine Dreams #51
metadata.description:
Dopamine is a chemical released in the brain that makes you feel good.

Dopamine Dreams is an exploration of using patterns and geometric forms to create something that also makes you feel good; to create something that feels natural, as if it has sprung from the ground or appeared in the sky.  

In this work, there is a conversation happening between two modes for drawing the same grid. One is tight, geometric and calm. The other is loose, loopy and excited. They overlap, interlace and compete to fill the space.  One cannot exist without the other. Balance is the the key. Between them they create a landscape in which to dream. 

Generative artwork by AutoEclectus

Controls in live mode:
- After animation stops, press [s] to save a png

@autoeclectus everywhere - Twitter, Instagram and Masterdon. 
https://autoeclectus.art

metadata.name: Der Ast #138
metadata.description:
Der Ast is a work which grew from a love of triganometry. The tree grows and branches 
based on a fixed and finite set of rules and while this leads to some very self-similar 
structures, in some cases, it generally allows for some very detailed complexity and 
surprise overall.

In this system, a box is drawn and on top of it, a right-angled triangle. The triangle
has an α angle conforming to a set formula (for example, in one system the angle follows)
a sinewave along the bough). From this triangle we construct the next square/triangle
set upon the hypotenuse and, if the β is wide enough, a second branch sprouts from the 
adjacent side.

This work is intended to be printed, and so included are controls to allow you to download
a high-resolution version as well as to create any aspect you wish.

- Append &dpr=x to the URL where DPR is the pixel density you want. This defaults to 2
- Append &fs=true to the URL to scale the token to the size of your browser
- Append &width=x and &height=y to the URL to scale the token to a specific size

Double-click/tap to download.
